9 WHEREAS, during his time as Mayor of the City of Yellville, Shawn Lane
10 led the city in a fiscally responsible manner and led several city projects
11 and improvement initiatives for Yellville, including creation of a rail spur
12 for the industrial park, moving and renovating the train station into the
13 current Heritage Society, adding upgrades to and creating an endowment for
14 Yellville City Park, restoring and expanding Layton Cemetery, funding
15 firemen's pensions and the Yellville Volunteer Fire Department, renovating
16 Yellville City Hall, and adding sidewalks on the downtown square; and
17
18 WHEREAS, Shawn Lane served on the Northwest Arkansas Economic
19 Development District, the Arkansas State Aid Street Committee, the Advisory
20 Board of the Yellville First Service Bank, the Board of Directors of the Twin
21 Lakes Community Foundation, and the Marion County Healthcare Association, and
22 was a longtime member of the Yellville Chamber of Commerce, through which he
23 was awarded Citizen of the Year in 2008 and 2013; and
24
25 WHEREAS, Shawn Lane could be found cooking hamburgers at Yellville-
26 Summit Panthers football games on Friday nights for over fifteen (15) years,
27 and he loved to host and grill out, bringing people together with his amazing
28 cooking and easygoing hospitality; and
